divs: sighting detailsat approx. 1:30am on 29 apr, i decided to use the sun obliteration photo technique on the full moon. using a nikon 5700, then transfd images to pc, then enlarged to 20000x15000, then altered brightness\contrast... i found something very unusual...very the 2nd photo taken at +10 seconds, the 3rd at +16 from photo 1 1 29aprmoon 2 29aprmoon_10sec 3 29aprmoon_16sec included are the hot links to fileden with the original photos and the ones i added text and changed brightness on. the originals so you can see and alter colors and etc for yourself and to see....well....i am puzzled as a frog in a toilet please tell me what in the *bleep* i took a photo of! http:\\www.fileden.com\files\2006\7\2\104905\\29aprmoon.jpg http:\\www.fileden.com\files\2006\7\2\104905\\29aprmoon copy.jpg http:\\www.fileden.com\files\2006\7\2\104905\\29aprmoon_10sec.jpg http:\\www.fileden.com\files\2006\7\2\104905\\29aprmoon_10sec copy.jpg http:\\www.fileden.com\files\2006\7\2\104905\\29aprmoon_16sec.jpg http:\\www.fileden.com\files\2006\7\2\104905\\29aprmoon_16sec copy.jpg oh, on the original photos, yes they are dark...lol, the flash was disabled, the moon rests\is masked behind a mounted susan b anthony coin, the moon is 'slightly' above dead center in all shots. i also sent this information to bill of ufo magazine\ufo hunters to answer the points: 1. just decided to use obliteraton techinque to photograph night sky 2. not noticed until i changed brightness on photos 3. lol...its not an aircraft, thats for sure 4. no, motion, still photos, but motion is seen from subsequent shots 5. i am dumbfounded! 6. they were not seen with naked eye, enlarged photos showed them
